He drove at Le Mans 14 times between 1971 and 1986, often in a car bearing his own name. After he and co-driver Chris Craft finished third in 1976, they drove a lap of honour before the British Grand Prix at Brands Hatch. He later moved into TV, presenting programmes including the long-running Victory By Design series. De Cadenet was born in London to an officer in the French services and his wife. He died after a long illness and is survived by his second wife and three children, including former TV host Amanda de Cadenet.